## Common Flags
- `-u` - Target URL for dir and vhost modes
- `-d` - Target domain name for dns mode
- `-w` - Path to the wordlist to use for brute forcing
- `-t` - Number of concurrent threads (default: 10); increase for faster scans
- `-x` - File extensions to append to each wordlist entry (comma-separated)
- `-s` - Whitelist specific HTTP status codes to display (comma-separated)
- `-b` - Blacklist HTTP status codes to hide from results (comma-separated)
- `-o` - Save output results to a specified file
- `-k` / `--no-tls-validation` - Skip TLS/SSL certificate validation for HTTPS targets
- `-r` - Follow HTTP redirects during directory scanning
- `-e` - Print full URLs in results instead of relative paths
- `-l` - Include the length of the response body in output
- `-q` - Quiet mode; suppress banner and progress updates, show results only
- `-v` - Verbose mode; display additional information including errors and misses
- `-c` - Send custom cookies with every request (e.g. session tokens)
- `-H` - Add a custom HTTP header to every request; can be used multiple times
- `-U` - Username for HTTP Basic Authentication
- `-P` - Password for HTTP Basic Authentication
- `-a` - Set a custom User-Agent string for all requests
- `--random-agent` - Use a randomly selected User-Agent string per request
- `--proxy` - Route all traffic through an HTTP or SOCKS5 proxy
- `--delay` - Add a delay between requests (e.g. `500ms`, `1s`) to reduce detection
- `--timeout` - HTTP request timeout duration (default: 10s)
- `--wildcard` - Force continuation of scan even when wildcard DNS responses are detected
- `--append-domain` - Append the base domain to each vhost wordlist entry automatically
- `--exclude-length` - Exclude responses of a specific body length from vhost results
- `--show-ips` - Show resolved IP addresses alongside discovered subdomains in dns mode
- `-r` - Custom DNS resolver IP address to use for dns mode (e.g. `8.8.8.8`)
- `-z` - Do not print progress to stdout during scanning
